results.title: Wombat tale
results.creator_credit: Robbie Sands and Animation and Interactive Media (AIM) RMIT
results.brief_description:
An interactive animation on CD-ROM set in 1953 which tells the story of four wombats who dig their way to Russia in search of tomatoes. The user plays the part of a Russian farmer whose farm becomes a haven for four idealist wombats.
In Russian with English subtitles

results.title: Woman sesame oil maker [NTSC]
results.creator_credit: Tianjin Film Studio, Changchun Film Studio and Xie Fei
results.brief_description: A successful career woman, the manager of a Chinese-Japanese joint venture sesame oil factory, seeks comfort from the stress of her business, a violent, alcoholic husband, and a mentally retarded son in the arms of a married man. When the young girl she has arranged to marry her son discovers her affair, she responds with sympathy to her future mother-in-law’s problems. A surprisingly close relationship develops between the two women as they struggle together against tradition and circumstance to take control of their lives. Cast includes Siqin Gaowa, Wu Yujuan, Lei Kesheng and Chen Baoguo. The film won the Golden Bear and Film Critic awards at the 43rd Berlin Film Festival 1993. In Mandarin with English subtitles.

results.title: Woman of the Year
results.creator_credit: Joseph L Mankiewicz, Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer and George Stevens
results.brief_description: In this sophisticated comedy, the initial venture of that impeccable partnership of Katharine Hepburn and Spencer Tracy, Hepburn plays a renowned columnist and celebrated expert on world affairs. Tracy works on the same newspaper as a sports writer. When Hepburn is nominated “Woman of the Year”, the fight is on between career and marriage.

results.title: Woman of the dunes = Suna no onna
results.creator_credit: Teshigahara Productions, Kiichi Ichikawa, Tadashi Ono and Hiroshi Teshigahara
results.brief_description: Out in the sand dunes a woman lives alone at the bottom of a pit. One day the local villagers bring a man to her. He can’t escape; gradually the two are drawn to each other. Out of this bizarre, if simple situation, Teshigahara builds an atmospheric, highly charged and remarkably sensual exploration of the human condition.

results.title: Woman is
results.brief_description: Uses a series of photographic stills in order to illustrate the history and character of the roles that women occupy in society. Stresses the contrast and individuality of the people within each role. The film is composed of approximately four hundred separate images of women collected from drawings, paintings and photographs. Music and sound effects compliment the quotes and comments about the situation of women throughout history.

results.title: Woman gathers food
results.brief_description:
Episode of Series “Alcheringa”.
To the women falls the task of collecting supplementary foods - such as witchetty grubs and yams. Use is made of a sharply pointed stick to dig under bark for grubs and to kill a lizard which wanders across their path; also to dig for yams. The daughter accompanies her mother on her daily walk and learns the art of food gathering.

results.title: Woman demon human = Ren Gui Qing [NTSC]
results.creator_credit: Shanghai Film Studio and Huang Shuqin
results.brief_description: Directed by one of China’s most prominent female directors this highly expressionistic, psychological drama, based on a true story, focuses on the unconventional career of a famous Chinese Opera actress. Told in flashbacks, the film traces her life on the stage from the 1950s to the 1980s. The initial hostility she receives from the public for embracing male roles, turns to admiration when, defying traditions and conventions, she becomes the first woman to play the lead male role in the Peking Opera. She becomes famous in her role as Zhong Kui, a great mythical character of Chinese theatre. The character gradually takes on a life of its own becoming an alter ego and sounding board for the actress. Impressive performances and cinematographic artistry combine to create a powerful, visually stunning tale. Cast includes Xu Shouli and Li Baotian. In Mandarin with English subtitles.

results.title: Woman as a flower = La Femme fleur
results.brief_description: Based on the drawings and etchings of Aubrey Beardsley, Gustav Klimt, Max Klinger and other artists living about the turn of the century. This film is a tribute to the women of the Edwardian era, and gives a fascinating glimpse of that time. Also of interest as a study of the Art Nouveau, which expressed the prosperity of the period.

results.title: Woman's estate
results.brief_description:
Episode number 12 of Series “Review: 28th year”.
